<hr size="1">
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">
		

<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>QUOTE OF THE DAY</b></font><br>

<font size="2">"Maybe we'll get that free drink when we get back on the
plane  if we get back on the plane." <br>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/nyregion/23AIRP.html?todaysheadlines">ANTHONY TRAMONTANA,</a>one of hundreds of passengers whose planes were called back
to the gates at La Guardia Airport.


<hr size="1">



<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>NATIONAL</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/national/23ANTH.html?todaysheadlines">Report Linking Anthrax and Hijackers Is Investigated</a></b><br>
A recent memo circulated among top government officials has renewed a debate about a connection between the Sept. 11 attacks and the anthrax letters.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/education/23EXAM.html?todaysheadlines">College Board to Revise SAT</a></b><br>
Responding to criticism that the SAT does not sufficiently reflect what is learned in the classroom, the College Board is planning to revamp the test.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/national/23OSCA.html?todaysheadlines">Security-Prone Oscar Ceremony a Blight on Business</a></b><br>
Security has come to the Academy Awards, transforming the event into what promises to be a vastly different experience for everyone from stars to gawking fans.
<P>
</font>













