<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>INTERNATIONAL</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/international/middleeast/23MIDE.html?todaysheadlines">Prodded by U.S., Israel Again Tries to Forge a Truce</a></b><br>
Negotiations between Israelis and Palestinians ended inconclusively on Friday, but will resume over the weekend despite the third suicide bombing in three days.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/international/asia/23STRA.html?todaysheadlines">U.S. Says It Found Qaeda Lab Being Built to Produce Anthrax</a></b><br>
The United States has discovered a laboratory under construction in Afghanistan where officials believe Al Qaeda planned to develop biological agents.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/international/23PREX.html?todaysheadlines">Bush, in Monterrey, Speaks of Conditional Global Aid</a></b><br>
Poor countries must be prepared to carry out reforms if they expect to receive increased aid, President Bush warned on Friday.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/world/index.html?todaysheadlines">MORE INTERNATIONAL NEWS</a>
