<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>ARTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/arts/23WOME.html?todaysheadlines">When Janie Came Marching Home: Women Fought in the Civil War</a></b><br>
History buffs, including Lauren M. Cook, set out to document the full story of women who went into combat during the Civil War.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/arts/23STUD.html?todaysheadlines">Debate? Dissent? Discussion? Oh, Don't Go There!</a></b><br>
That familiar interjection "whatever" says a lot about the state of mind of college students today. So do the catch phrases "no problem," "not even" and "don't go there."
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/23/arts/theater/23GOLD.html?todaysheadlines">A Dated Musical Whose Music Is Never Out of Date</a></b><br>
Precious things lose their luster fast in "Golden Boy," the 1964 musical inspired by Clifford Odets's hit drama of 1937.
<P>
</font>













